WikifierOutput.InputText: Wednesday, October 8, 2008 | | | | | | | WEATHER FOR STROUDSBURG: P/CLOUDY 33° Strangeland finishes 10th in Norway Run Text Size: | | Share October 08, 2008 NEW YORK — East Stroudsburg South freshman Dylan Strangeland finished 10th in his age group in the 1.7-mile Norway Run in Central Park on Saturday. Strangeland, who finished 168th overall, ran 11:27 for the race, averaging 6:44 a mile. His aunt, Nancy Gramberg of Blairstown, finished 8th in the 55-59 age group in a time of 27:16. There were 1,751 runners in the event.
